<p>The <code>scale</code> utility classes visually resize elements using
<code>transform: scale()</code>.</p>
<h3 id="doc-syntax">Syntax</h3>
<pre><code>[state]:scale-[ratio]</code></pre>
<ul>
<li><strong>[state]</strong> – <em>(optional)</em> <code>hover</code> or
<code>focus</code>.</li>
<li><strong>[ratio]</strong> – The desired scale percentage
(e.g. <code>105</code> → 105% → <code>scale(1.05)</code>)</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="doc-usage-examples">Usage Examples</h3>
<div class="scale-90 w-fit mt-4 border rounded p-2">
Scaled to 90%
</div>
<pre class="html"><code>&lt;!-- Static scale --&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;scale-90&quot;&gt;Scaled to 90%&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
<div class="hover:scale-110 w-fit mt-4 border rounded p-2">
Scales to 110% on hover
</div>
<pre class="html"><code>&lt;!-- On hover --&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;hover:scale-110&quot;&gt;Scales to 110% on hover&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
<p><input type="text" class="form-control focus:scale-105 w-fit mt-4 p-2" placeholder="Click to focus"/></p>
<pre class="html"><code>&lt;!-- On focus --&gt;
&lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; class=&quot;form-control focus-scale-105&quot; /&gt;</code></pre>
